{"word":"κωκύω","slug":"κωκύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κωκύω</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to shriek, cry, wail</i>, mostly of women, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to wail over</i> one dead, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}